4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, upon the submission of an
6 approval petition to the State Oil and Gas Board, a
7 storage facility for gas must be approved by the board
8 after notice and hearing before operating in the state.
9 This bill would require the petition and any
10 supporting documentation also be submitted to any local
11 government with jurisdiction over the area of the
12 proposed facility.
13 This bill would authorize such a local
14 government to submit comments to the board regarding
15 the petition and participate in the hearing of the
16 board on the petition.
17 Also under existing rule of the State Oil and
18 Gas Board, a storage facility that is used for the
19 storage and sequestration of carbon dioxide is assessed
20 certain fees.
21 This bill would require carbon dioxide storage
22 facilities be assessed certain fees on each ton of
23 carbon dioxide injected for disbursement to the state
24 and county in which the injection occurred.
25 This bill would also establish the Study
26 Commission on Carbon Dioxide Storage Facility Fees to
27 assess certain topics regarding levying fees on carbon
28 dioxide storage facilities.
